name: Latent Eye
description: Eye's are an important part of who we are as humans, and- although we can adapt- this intricate sense is weird and archaic. As we age, we change the way we interact with it. Starting as babies, with little comprehension on anything. Ending, hopefully, with enough memory that all we see is tied to the past in some memory- consuming what is with what was. And then when we die, the memory dispersed in death. Where we are without biological memory or senses at all. Home.
